HEADWORD: Systematist
<hw>Sys"tem*a*tist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>syst⟦eacute⟧matiste</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who forms a
system, or reduces to system.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who adheres to a system.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Systematization</ent>⟦br⟧
